					<p>The wheels of the fake news mills never stop! Obviously &#8220;Fatty&#8221; killed his brother. He has killed many of his relatives and loyal toadies. South Korea is of course gleeful over this poke in China&#8217;s eye. South Korea has suffered like no other country from N. Korean terrorist attacks. Civilian airliners were bombed out of the sky, S. Korean diplomats were murdered in broad daylight in Bangkok, a S. Korean naval vessel was blown out of he water by a N. Korean torpedo, a S. Korean town on a small island was shelled by N. Korean artillery, N. Korea has exploded nuclear devices and shot off ballistic missiles and all we ever heard from China was &#8220;We call for restraint.&#8221; China has been N. Korea&#8217;s principal source of EVERYTHING for decades now. It has facilitated N. Korean bad behavior and now the dog has bitten the hand that feeds it. When will China wake up? The stationing of THAAD is a direct result of China&#8217;s support for the Kim regime.</p>
